<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>International&#174; DT 466E, DT 466, 530, 530E, and HT 530 Diesel Engines - Vibration Damper, Crankshaft,
        Main Bearings, Flywheel, and Crankcase - Install - Flywheel
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s210010704.4" graphiccount="9">
        <title>Flywheel</title>
        <svcsubproc id="s210010704.4.1">
            <title>Install Flywheel</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>When installing 148 tooth ring gear flywheel (approximate 18.70 inch outside diameter), make
                        sure two bolts in engine mounts on side of flywheel housing are loosened enough to allow
                        installation of flywheel with ring gear. These bolts are lowest and rear most bolts on the
                        engine mounts. After installation, torque engine mount bolts to "
                        <hotlnk document="eges2101_205.xml" xrefid="t210010703">Special Torque</hotlnk>
                        ."
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install two flywheel guide studs from
                    <hotlnk document="eges2101_206.xml" xrefid="t210010704">Guide Stud Set (ZTSE4375)</hotlnk>
                    in 3 and 9 o'clock positions of crankshaft.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install flywheel over guide studs, fasten flywheel to crankshaft with ten flywheel
                    mounting bolts.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>For applications using automatic transmissions, install spacer, flexplate(s) and reinforcing
                        ring, and then install ten flywheel mounting bolts.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f210010765" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figeg5/EG5098.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                <caption>Install flywheel guide studs</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove two guide studs and install remaining two mounting bolts. Tighten all twelve
                    flywheel mounting bolts to "
                    <hotlnk document="eges2101_205.xml" xrefid="t210010703">Special Torque</hotlnk>
                    ."
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f210010766" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figeg5/EG5097.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                <caption>Install and torque flywheel</caption>
            </figure>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc id="s210010704.4.2">
            <title>Vehicles Equipped with Allison 2000 Series Transmissions</title>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>For vehicles equipped with Allison 2000 series transmission only. If this is a vehicle
                        re-configuration (not previously equipped with Allison 2000 series). Correct part number
                        flywheel housing must be used. Failure to do so will cause interference between the flexplate
                        studs and the flywheel housing. This will be evident only after the transmission has been
                        installed.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install two guide pins from
                    <hotlnk document="eges2101_206.xml" xrefid="t210010704">Guide Stud Set (ZTSE4375)</hotlnk>
                    at 3 and 9 o'clock positions.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Slide Adapter hub over guide pins.</para>
                <figure id="f210010767" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figeg8/EG8964.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                    <caption>Install adapter hub</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">Adapter hub</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">Guide pins</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Slide flywheel assembly over guide pins and over adapter hub.</para>
                <figure id="f210010768" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figeg8/EG8965.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                    <caption>Install flywheel assembly</caption>
                </figure>
                <specpara>
                    <caution>
                        <para>To avoid possible engine or transmission damage, install reinforcing ring, with stamped 4
                            digit number on ring facing outward (toward the transmission). If part number is not
                            visible, install with previous paint mark facing toward transmission. Failure to install
                            this part correctly may result in premature flexplate failure.
                        </para>
                    </caution>
                    <note>
                        <para>Ring gear is offset (not centered) on flywheel. Flywheel must be installed so ring gear is
                            offset away from engine, toward transmission.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Slide reinforcing ring over guide pins.</para>
                <figure id="f210010769" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figeg8/EG8966.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                    <caption>Install reinforcement ring</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">Reinforcement ring</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">Guide pins</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install ten flywheel mounting bolts.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove two guide pins and install two remaining mounting bolts.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Torque twelve flywheel mounting bolts to "
                    <hotlnk document="eges2101_205.xml" xrefid="t210010703">Special Torque</hotlnk>
                    ."
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc id="s210010704.4.3">
            <title>Vehicles Equipped with MT-640/650 Transmissions</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install two guide pins from
                    <hotlnk document="eges2101_206.xml" xrefid="t210010704">Guide Stud Set (ZTSE4375)</hotlnk>
                    at 3 and 9 o'clock positions.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install flywheel over guide pins.</para>
                <figure id="f210010770" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figeg8/EG8968.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                    <caption>Install flywheel</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">Flywheel</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">Large hole in flywheel</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
                <specpara>
                    <caution>
                        <para>To avoid possible engine or transmission damage, small bolt holes in flexplate for torque
                            converter must line up with large holes in flywheel.
                        </para>
                    </caution>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install flexplate over guide pins with logo and part number toward transmission. If part
                    number and logo are not visible, face previous paint mark toward transmission.
                </para>
                <figure id="f210010771" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figeg8/EG8969.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                    <caption>Install flexplate</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">Flexplate</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">Small holes in flexplate</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
                <specpara>
                    <caution>
                        <para>To avoid possible engine or transmission damage, install reinforcing ring, with stamped 4
                            digit number on ring facing outward (toward the transmission). If part number is not
                            visible, install with previous paint mark facing toward transmission. Failure to install
                            this part correctly may result in premature flexplate failure.
                        </para>
                    </caution>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Slide reinforcement ring over guide pins.</para>
                <figure id="f210010772" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figeg8/EG8970.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                    <caption>Install reinforcement ring</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">Reinforcement ring</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">Guide pins</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install ten flywheel mounting bolts.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove two guide pins and install two remaining mounting bolts.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Torque twelve flywheel mounting bolts to "
                    <hotlnk document="eges2101_205.xml" xrefid="t210010703">Special Torque</hotlnk>
                    ."
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc id="s210010704.4.4">
            <title>Vehicles Equipped with MD-3060 and 3570 or D-4000 Transmissions</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install two guide pins from
                    <hotlnk document="eges2101_206.xml" xrefid="t210010704">Guide Stud Set (ZTSE4375)</hotlnk>
                    at 3 and 9 o'clock positions.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Flexplate assembly is available as a service part completely assembled.</para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Slide flexplate assembly over guide pins with adapter hub toward engine.</para>
                <figure id="f210010773" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figeg8/EG8971.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                    <caption>Install flywheel assembly</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">Flywheel assembly</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">Adapter hub</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install ten flywheel mounting bolts.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove two guide pins and install two remaining mounting bolts.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Torque twelve flywheel mounting bolts to "
                    <hotlnk document="eges2101_205.xml" xrefid="t210010703">Special Torque</hotlnk>
                    ."
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
